# shadcn UI Component Guidelines

This project uses **shadcn UI** for all UI elements.

## Initialization

If shadcn UI is not initialized in the project, use the following command:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

## Adding Components

When you need a particular component that is not yet installed, use the following command format:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>
```

### Examples

- To install the button component:
  ```bash
  npx shadcn@latest add button
  ```

- To install the card component:
  ```bash
  npx shadcn@latest add card
  ```

- To install the dialog component:
  ```bash
  npx shadcn@latest add dialog
  ```

## Usage Guidelines

### CRITICAL RULE: shadcn UI ONLY

**ABSOLUTELY NO CUSTOM UI COMPONENTS ARE ALLOWED IN THIS PROJECT.**

- **ONLY use shadcn UI components** for ALL UI elements
- **NEVER create custom buttons, cards, dialogs, inputs, or any other UI elements**
- **NEVER write custom Tailwind classes for UI components** - use shadcn UI components exclusively
- If a UI element is needed, find the appropriate shadcn UI component or install it
- Check if a component is already installed before adding it
- Components are typically installed in the `components/ui` directory
- Follow shadcn UI's component API and patterns

### Examples of What NOT to Do

❌ **NEVER do this:**
```tsx
// BAD - Custom button with Tailwind classes
<button className="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-500 rounded">Click me</button>
```

✅ **ALWAYS do this:**
```tsx
// GOOD - shadcn UI Button component
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
<Button>Click me</Button>
```

❌ **NEVER do this:**
```tsx
// BAD - Custom card with divs
<div className="border rounded-lg p-4 shadow">
  <h2>Title</h2>
  <p>Content</p>
</div>
```

✅ **ALWAYS do this:**
```tsx
// GOOD - shadcn UI Card component
import { Card, CardHeader, CardTitle, CardContent } from '@/components/ui/card';
<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <CardTitle>Title</CardTitle>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>
    <p>Content</p>
  </CardContent>
</Card>
```

## Clerk Integration with shadcn UI

**ALL Clerk authentication UI MUST use shadcn UI components.**

### Sign In / Sign Up Buttons

- **Use shadcn UI Button component** for all Clerk sign in and sign up triggers
- **Use shadcn UI Dialog component** to display Clerk's authentication UI in a modal
- **NEVER use Clerk's default button styling or prebuilt components directly in the UI**

### Implementation Pattern

```tsx
'use client';

import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import {
  Dialog,
  DialogContent,
  DialogDescription,
  DialogHeader,
  DialogTitle,
  DialogTrigger,
} from '@/components/ui/dialog';
import { SignIn, SignUp } from '@clerk/nextjs';

// ✅ CORRECT - Sign In with shadcn UI
export function SignInButton() {
  return (
    <Dialog>
      <DialogTrigger asChild>
        <Button>Sign In</Button>
      </DialogTrigger>
      <DialogContent>
        <DialogHeader>
          <DialogTitle>Sign In</DialogTitle>
          <DialogDescription>
            Sign in to your account
          </DialogDescription>
        </DialogHeader>
        <SignIn />
      </DialogContent>
    </Dialog>
  );
}

// ✅ CORRECT - Sign Up with shadcn UI
export function SignUpButton() {
  return (
    <Dialog>
      <DialogTrigger asChild>
        <Button variant="outline">Sign Up</Button>
      </DialogTrigger>
      <DialogContent>
        <DialogHeader>
          <DialogTitle>Create Account</DialogTitle>
          <DialogDescription>
            Create a new account to get started
          </DialogDescription>
        </DialogHeader>
        <SignUp />
      </DialogContent>
    </Dialog>
  );
}
```

### Required shadcn UI Components for Clerk

Install these shadcn UI components for Clerk integration:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
npx shadcn@latest add dialog
```

### Key Rules for Clerk Integration

- ✅ Use shadcn UI `Button` for all authentication triggers
- ✅ Use shadcn UI `Dialog` to wrap Clerk's `<SignIn />` and `<SignUp />` components
- ✅ Apply shadcn UI button variants for different states (default, outline, ghost, etc.)
- ❌ NEVER use `<SignInButton>` or `<SignUpButton>` from `@clerk/nextjs` directly
- ❌ NEVER create custom styled buttons for authentication
- ❌ NEVER embed Clerk components directly on the page without a modal

## Component Installation Reference

Common shadcn UI components you may need:

- `button` - For all clickable actions
- `card` - For content containers
- `dialog` - For modals (including Clerk auth)
- `form` - For form inputs
- `input` - For text inputs
- `label` - For form labels
- `select` - For dropdowns
- `textarea` - For multi-line text inputs
- `alert` - For notifications
- `badge` - For labels and tags
- `table` - For data tables
- `tabs` - For tabbed interfaces
- `toast` - For toast notifications

Always check the [shadcn UI documentation](https://ui.shadcn.com) for available components.
